The focus of the course is on Old, Middle and Early Modern English. Original texts are used to explain the regularities and the socio-historical reasons underlying language change. During the course, the students will analyse and translate original texts from different periods using digital databases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aims of the course are:  (1) to introduce the development of the English language in socio-historical context;  (2) to give basic knowledge of Old and Middle English, comparing the language used in different periods;  (3) to understand the irregularities of contemporary English (why and how has change occurred).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course, the student: - Identifies the general regularities of the diachronic change of English in a text - Explains the irregularities of Present Day English - Analyses the development of English in the socio-historical context - Reads short original texts in Old, Middle and Late Middle English - Applies digital tools and self-regulated learning skills for composing a group project - Translates original texts from Old and Middle English into Present Day English using digital databases
